<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="26" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,821,1290]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,341,1141,1167]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronymic, based on the Latinized surname of the fictional Don Quijote, immortalized in the famous novel &quot;Don Quijote de la Mancha&quot; written by Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra and first published in 
<number box="[519,581,1224,1250]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="1605.0">1605</number>
. This species is named to commemorate the 
<number box="[1101,1145,1224,1250]" pageId="3" pageNumber="26" value="400.0">400</number>
th anniversary of publication of this important piece of Spanish literature.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
